        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1946-05-14T05:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1946-05-14T05:00:00-05:00" n="600" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d600">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">865.00/5–1446: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in the Soviet Union</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Smith</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">confidential</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Moscow</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1946-05-14T13:00:00+03:00">May 14, 1946—1 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received 8:50 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1518. Redeptel 849, May 8. Inasmuch as the British Embassy in Moscow already
                    received in a letter dated May 12 from Lozovski, a reply to its frequent
                    approaches to the Soviet Govt on the question of the “institutional truce” in
                    Italy, I have not approached the Soviet Govt in this regard as instructed.
                    Soviet reply to British states that Soviet Govt does not object to proposal to
                    inform Italian Govt that Allied Govts no longer consider as remaining in force
                    the undertakings given by Italian Govt in respect of institutional truce.</p>
                <p>Text of full reply in translation has been sent by British Embassy to Washington
                    and assume Dept will be able to obtain a complete copy.<note n="11" xml:id="d600fn11">Not printed.</note>
                </p>
                <p>Repeated London 247.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Smith</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
